name: arkit_scenes
title: ARKit Scenes
description: Visualizes the ARKitScenes dataset using the Rerun SDK. The dataset contains color+depth images, the reconstructed mesh and labeled bounding boxes around furniture.

name: structure_from_motion
title: Structure From Motion
description: An example using Rerun to log and visualize the output of COLMAP's sparse reconstruction. COLMAP is a general-purpose Structure-from-Motion (SfM) and Multi-View Stereo (MVS) pipeline with a graphical and command-line interface. In this example a short video clip has been processed offline by the COLMAP pipeline, and we use Rerun to visualize the individual camera frames, estimated camera poses, and resulting point clouds over time.

name: dicom_mri
title: Dicom MRI
description: Example using a DICOM MRI scan. This demonstrates the flexible tensor slicing capabilities of the Rerun viewer.

name: human_pose_tracking
title: Human Pose Tracking
description: Use the MediaPipe Pose solution to detect and track a human pose in video.

name: plots
title: Plots
description: Simple example of plots and charts.

name: detect_and_track_objects
title: Detect and Track Objects
description: Applying simple object detection and segmentation on a video using the Huggingface `transformers` library. Tracking across frames is performed using CSRT from OpenCV.

name: dna
title: Helix
description: Simple example of logging line primitives to draw a 3D helix.
